
Overview of noun thong

The noun thong has 5 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) lash, thong -- (leather strip that forms the flexible part of a whip)
2. thong -- (underpants resembling a G-string; worn by women especially under very tight pants; "she wore thongs in her quest for the callipygian ideal")
3. thong -- (a thin strip of leather; often used to lash things together)
4. G-string, thong -- (minimal clothing worn by stripteasers; a narrow strip of fabric that covers the pubic area, passes between the thighs, and is supported by a waistband)
5. flip-flop, thong -- (a backless sandal held to the foot by a thong between the big toe and the second toe)
